Hi @dimdenGD, I'm debugging `ultimate-express` and I have see that each middleware require a long round trip into `_routeRequest` of `router.js`, I want try to optimeze it, eg.:

```js
app.use(responseTime());
app.use(express.json({ limit: "100mb" }));
app.use(compression({ threshold: 1 }));
```

these middleware require to be applied into every route path, there isn't a way for make a short round trip into `_routeRequest` and make it faster?

Hey, I wanted to try this with my app but for a regex route with /*, ultimate express has a req.params different to express. Here's a simple reproduction:

```bash
npm i express ultimate-express
```
```javascript
const express = require('express');
// const express = require('ultimate-express');

const app = express();
app.get('/test/*', (req, res) => {
    console.log(req.params);
    res.send('Hello');
})
const port = 3000;
app.listen(port, () => {
    console.log(`Server is running on port ${port}`);
});
```

Then load localhost:3000/test/hello

The req.params is {} for ultimate express and { '0': 'hello' } for express.
